column10:
Good game overall. Finally a solid Jagged Alliance sequel after so many fails...However it does have some things I do not like. For example;

I do not like how the game forces me to reposition all my mercs to a random location all grouped up at the start of DEFENSIVE battle!....

Also, I am not a fan of how night combat works, it was much better in JA2 where night reduces your vision (how far ahead you can see) whereas in JA3 it reduces you accuracy...
